Feature: Files Upload

  Background:
    Given I am authenticated

  Scenario: Upload single file successfully

    When I upload a file to "/api/v1/file/upload" with:
      | id    | 019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846 |
      | files | test-document.pdf                     |

    Then the response status code should be 200
    Then the response body should contain:
    """
    [
      {
        "id": "${json-unit.regex}^[0-9a-fA-F]{8}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{12}$",
        "fileName": "test-document.pdf",
        "urlS3": "${json-unit.regex}^https://.*\\.s3\\.amazonaws\\.com/.*$",
        "size": "${json-unit.any-number}",
        "createdAt": "${json-unit.any-string}"
      }
    ]
    """
    Then the table "files" should have 1 records

  Scenario: Upload multiple files successfully

    When I upload files to "/api/v1/file/upload" with:
      | id    | 019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846 |
      | files | test-document.pdf,image.jpg,data.xlsx |

    Then the response status code should be 200
    Then the response body should have 3 items
    Then the table "files" should have 3 records

  Scenario: Upload file with large size

    When I upload a file to "/api/v1/file/upload" with:
      | id    | 019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846 |
      | files | large-file.zip                        |
      | size  | 10485760                              |

    Then the response status code should be 200
    Then the response body should contain:
    """
    [
      {
        "id": "${json-unit.regex}^[0-9a-fA-F]{8}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{12}$",
        "fileName": "large-file.zip",
        "urlS3": "${json-unit.regex}^https://.*\\.s3\\.amazonaws\\.com/.*$",
        "size": 10485760,
        "createdAt": "${json-unit.any-string}"
      }
    ]
    """

